column5: just got back from temagami , lots of rain fridya 10 inches of snow saturday make for on slushy ride back  pics to follow
what about the fish??  you cant go to temagami and not give a fishing report.
Yah Malcolm... what he said ! lol  Hear there's still 24 to 28 inches of ice though...

lots of ice wayne , but shore line was staring in places to break up ice road at landing is now closed even though we saw lots of tire marks inthe slush, didnt go to fish up to do a work weekend with my buddy rick and ray , to get ricks camp ready , crapy weather , and only thing open was white fish
work ? temagami? no fishing?   ...something wrong with this picture...
ive gone up to temagami to work several times as well, but work is no excuse not to fish on that lake, its like a fishing sin or something.
and so close to easter...yup its a fishin sin for sure...he will have to kneel on his fishing rod and pray for forgivness

I've seen these 3 guys fish. There would have been nothing to report anyways.  Glad you got the roof done malcolm. Shame you didn't get Rick back up to clear the trail into my new moose stand though. Looks like it'll be you and me in that new spot unless Rick sells it out to the guys in the first week.
welcome to zone 11 the crapshoot zone! unless you LOVE to perch fish after march 16th
Translation-    We fished our butts off and didn't catch a thing!
Hahaha thats true there are a pile of them around here too!  IGA No Frills Independednt.
